Recursive function call

This test exploits the fact that all
variables are static and local. We can
use a local variable as a counter for
how deep we are calling.
=========
void a() {
    int i = 1;
    
    printf("a");

    if (i >= 20) {
        i = 0;
        return;
    } else {
        i++;
        a();
    }
}

void main() {
    printf("b");
    a();
    printf("c");
}
